properties.areaDesc: Duluth MN to Port Wing WI; Two Harbors to Duluth MN
properties.headline: Heavy Freezing Spray Warning issued January 11 at 3:55AM CST until January 11 at 10:00PM CST by NWS Duluth MN
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Heavy Freezing Spray Warning, heavy freezing
spray at a rate of 2 cm per hour or greater expected, and may
rapidly accumulate on vessels. For the Small Craft Advisory,
east winds 10 to 20 knots with gusts up to 30 knots and waves
3 to 6 feet expected.

* WHERE...Two Harbors to Duluth MN and Duluth MN to Port Wing WI.

* WHEN...For the Heavy Freezing Spray Warning, from 3 PM this
afternoon to 10 PM CST this evening. For the Small Craft
Advisory, from 10 AM this morning to 4 PM CST Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Operating a vessel in heavy freezing spray is
hazardous. Freezing spray may render mechanical and electronic
components inoperative. Rapid ice accretion on decks and
superstructures may result in a catastrophic loss of stability.
Conditions will be hazardous to small craft.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should prepare for dangerous accumulation of ice on
their vessel. If possible, remain in port, avoid the warning area
or conduct mitigation.

Anyone operating a smaller vessel should avoid navigating in
hazardous conditions.

NWSheadline: SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 10 AM THIS MORNING TO 4 PM CST SUNDAY... ...HEAVY FREEZING SPRAY WARNING IN EFFECT FROM 3 PM THIS AFTERNOON TO 10 PM CST THIS EVENING
